{"aid": "http://arxiv.org/abs/2504.09911v1", "title": "Higher Chow cycles on Eisenstein K3 surfaces", "summary": "We construct higher Chow cycles of type (2,1) on some families of K3 surfaces
with non-symplectic automorphisms of order 3 and prove that our cycles are
indecomposable for very general members. The proof is a combination of some
degeneration arguments, and explicit computations of the regulator map.", "main_category": "math.AG", "categories": "math.AG", "published": "2025-04-14T06:18:07Z"}
